The paper discusses the use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) for text generation, which is a topic that falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new evaluation metric for GAN-based text generation, which involves approximating the distribution of generated text and evaluating it with traditional probability-based language model metrics. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) since GANs are commonly used in image generation tasks, and the paper proposes a new evaluation metric that could potentially be applied to GAN-based image generation as well.
